2T oil
1 onion, diced
2 bell peppers, diced
2T curry powder
1t ground cumin
4 cloves garlic, minced
1T ground ginger
2T cider vinegar
1.25c water
1 mango, diced
2lb chicken, cubed
0.33c raisins
0.5c coconut milk

Heat oil in saute pan over medium heat.  Cook onions until soft, add bell peppers.  If anything sticks, add a bit more oil.  Add curry and cumin, cook briefly.  Add ginger and garlic, cook briefly.

Add vinegar, water, and mango.  Increase heat to boil, then lower to a simmer for 15 minutes.  Puree sauce in a blender, return to pan.

Salt chicken, then add to pan with raisins.  Cover and cook until chicken is done, about 10 minutes.  Reduce heat to low, add coconut milk and let cook for another minute.  Grind in pepper to taste.
